body: $DMYI The main hypothesis of "bashers" that "all SPACs fall after merger" was finally disproved.
Here you have some recent deSPACs - speculative low floaters:
EFTR max SP 40+
ARQQ max SP 26
IRNT max SP 39 (AH)
For months "no one" wanted the above-mentioned and they stayed flat at 10.
I told you that SPACs will be back in play but you weren't listening.
And now RKLB - today max 20.88. The last one neared 10B in market cap and certainly is not a low floater.
Now let's make a comparison of EV/EBIDTA between RKLB and DMYI/IONQ.

RKLB has EBIDTA estmate for 2026 of 340M while IONQ - 272M. Current EV of IONQ is  1.38B and today's peak EV of RKLB was ca. 9.3B. This indicates EV/EBIDTA (2026) of 27.3. Equalizing this multiple gives potential SP of IONQ of ca. 34. This is pure mathematics.
If you oppose to that tell me ANY SINGLE REASON why IONQ should have lower EV/EBIDTA than RKLB. I am open to discussion.
